iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories At least 30 people are feared dead after a bus they were travelling in reportedly sideswiped a haulage truck and caught fire in Nyamatikiti River near Chaka in Chirumanzu.Harare - Zimbabwe police say as many as 17 people are feared dead after a bus went up in flames on Wednesday night after colliding with a truck.Police spokesperson Charity Charamba said on Thursday that more than 40 other people suffered serious injuries.She says people were trapped in the bus and died before help could arrive.Charamba says the bus was travelling to neighbouring South Africa from the capital, Harare.Road accidents are common in Zimbabwe, with many attributed to bad roads and speeding.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.